The paper deals with the problem of pulmonary nodule detection using deep learning techniques. Specifically, it proposes a novel framework using the ensemble of 2D CNNs using single views for false positive reduction. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of an autoencoder for non-nodule categorization, which involves unsupervised learning and clustering, indicating the involvement of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) techniques. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
